cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SD, cs.DB, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with mining user similarities over fully dynamic graph streams, which involves topics such as graph mining, similarity estimation, and stream processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes a sketch method that processes each edge in the graph stream with small time complexity and uses small memory space, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper deals with graph streams, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.DB (Databases) as well. Finally, the paper proposes a method to estimate user similarities over time, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
